&lt;h1 id="free-markets-are-intrinsic-to-humans"&gt;Free Markets Are Intrinsic to Humans&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mar 5 2019&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We use credits and debits to cooperate across genetic boundaries&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naval:&lt;/strong&gt;
Overall capitalism [meaning free markets] is intrinsic to the human species. Capitalism is not something we invented. Capitalism is not even something we discovered. It is in us in every exchange that we have.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Heresy</title><link>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/heresy/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/heresy/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_zh/heresy/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
